Commentary: OUT! LBW! Asitha Fernando cries for the appeal and the Umpire raises his finger this time! Harry Brook opts for a review! Asitha Fernando comes from over the wicket and bowls fuller on off, shaping it in vigorously. Harry Brook looks to flick it but misses and wears it on the front pad. The review pops up and shows there's no bat involvement on Ultra Edge and the Ball Tracking turns yellow as the ball hits the stump. Commentary: OUT! TAKEN! Excellent catch in the deep! That is some athletic stuff! The trails of bumpers have worked for Fernando. Bangs a bouncer on middle and leg. Gus Atkinson clears his front leg and looks to go for the big one but fails to find the elevation he wants. The ball loops towards the gap of deep mid-wicket and deep square leg, where Milan Rathnayake runs from the deep mid-wicket to his right and magnetizes himself towards the skier. He backtracks a bit and tumbles towards the boundary fence to get the catch safe into his pair of hands. The crowd is on its feet applauding the catch as well as the knock from Gus Atkinson.
Default_Commentary: 99.3: Asitha Fernando to Gus Atkinson, OUT! c Milan Rathnayake b Asitha Fernando.

Commentary: That is a peach of a delivery! Not sure how he didn't get a wicket there, very unlucky. Milan Rathnayake from 'over the wicket hits the length hard, on off, jags back in sharply, Ollie Pope tries to play at it with hard hands, but gets cut in half as the ball hits him on the back pad. There is a huge appeal for LBW, but not given. Ollie Pope takes the review just in time. UltraEdge confirms no bat involved and Ball Tracking shows that it is just going over the wickets. Pope survives and Lanka lose a review!

Commentary: OUT! TAKEN! One of the most bizarre dismissals you will ever see! Sri Lanka goes with the short-ball ploy here with a packed leg side field. Fernando as expected bangs this into the pitch around middle, Ollie Pope is aware of the tactics and moves to the leg side to access the other side, gets on top of the bounce as well, but unfortunately for him, he picks up the only fielder on the off side at deep point. Prabath Jayasuriya makes absolutely no mistake. Pope's struggles continues in this series!

Commentary: OUT! LBW! A huge shout for appeal and the umpire raises his finger this time! Jamie Smith opts for a review now! Jamie Smith gets down on his knee to sweep it away but misses on the inner edge and it thumps his lower pad. The review shows that there's no involvement with the bat and the Ball Tracking pops up three reds. The long and sturdy partnership of Smith and Root comes to an end!

Commentary: OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Matthew Potts has been strangled down the leg side and Asitha Fernando gets his man. This one lands just back of a length and at the body of the batter, Potts goes on to clip it away, but the ball passes really close to his gloves and through to the keeper where Dinesh Chandimal gobbles it up. A small inquiry about the catch, but the umpire is not interested. However, Dhananjaya de Silva takes the review after some discussions with his players and it turns out to be a great decision. UltraEdge shows a marginal spike when the ball passes the gloves and the on-field decision is overturned. Potts' short stay comes to an end!

Commentary: FOUR! RECORD ALERT! There it is, the moment everyone was waiting for! Joe Root surpasses Alastair Cook for the most centuries by an English player and writes his name in the history books. He does that with his fastest ton in just 111 balls. Root now also holds the record for the most number of runs by an English batter at Lord's and this is the first time he has managed two centuries in a Test match. Lahiru Kumara bangs this short and on leg, Joe Root moves to the leg side to access the off side and crunches it away through extra covers for a boundary. He punches jumps and punches the air in absolute delight and the crowd is up on its feet as well to applause this remarkable milestone.

Commentary: OUT! TAKEN! Is that it? No, It looks like Joe Root is staying and England have not declared yet. Lahiru Kumara bowls another good bumper, on middle and leg, Olly Stone tries to hook it away, but the ball gets big on him, it takes the top edge and flies toward the fine leg fence, Pathum Nissanka keeps his eyes on the ball, settles under it as it is wobbling in the air, takes a really good catch. Nine down for England now!

Commentary: OUT! EDGED AND GONE! Olly Stone gets Pathum Nissanka for the second time in this Test! The leg slip is in place for him again, but Stone lands this one on a good length just around off, shoots up and nips away a shy bit, Pathum Nissanka gets stranded in his crease and tries to push at it with only his hands, gets a thick outside edge that goes straight into the bread basket of Joe Root at first slip. Commentary: That one was close! Fuller length, around off. Angelo Mathews eases it towards deep third man. This looks close. The batters almost collided with each other during the second run, and they decided late for the third one, Dimuth Karunaratne once again is a bit casual, and the replay shows that he just about makes his ground.

Commentary: OUT! TAKEN! Shoaib Bashir strikes now! The change of angle works for and he gets a big wicket here. Bashir goes around the wicket and floats this one up, full and around off, invites the batter to have a go at it, Angelo Mathews decides to take it on and tries to drive it on the up, but this one turns in a bit more than expected, and he ends up hitting it much straighter and aerially towards mid off, Chris Woakes runs to his left and pouches it safely. Commentary: A loud appeal and given! Chandimal reviews. Is the impact outside off? NOT OUT! There is a spike on Ultra Edge as it passes the bat and the on-field decision has to be overturned. Don't think Chandimal himself felt an inside edge there. Length and around off. This lands and jags back in. Chandimal looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads. Commentary: OUT! IN THE AIR... AND TAKEN! Chris Woakes gets the job done for England! He comes 'round the wicket and bowls another slower one. Overpitches the delivery and on off. ENGLAND BEATS SRI LANKA BY A MARGIN OF 190 RUNS!
